    "narrative": "Our most potent offensive opportunities today are anchored by **Tyler Freeman** and **Will Smith**, who grade out as our clear top-tier starters with efficiency scores of 72.83 and 71.28, respectively. **Tyler Freeman** benefits from a high-ceiling matchup against Sasaki, where his 14% park advantage and a favorable 5.52 xERA from the opposition suggest significant upside. **Will Smith** follows a similar profile, utilizing a prime #3 hole placement and a massive 14% park boost to exploit a vulnerable matchup against Lorenzen. Meanwhile, **Jonathan Aranda** and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** provide reliable high-floor production, with **Jonathan Aranda** specifically benefiting from a wind-out scenario and a robust 12% platoon boost that elevates his profile to a 66.50 score.\n\nPlatoon edges remain a primary driver of today\u2019s construction, evidenced by **Gleyber Torres** and **Wenceel Perez** both seeing double-digit adjustments to their projections despite facing the elite 2.86 xERA of Crochet. While the risk of a high-end pitcher like Crochet necessitates caution, the dynamic platoon advantage keeps them in the lineup, though **Gleyber Torres** sits just above our marginal threshold. The most difficult personnel decision centered on **Matt Chapman**, who fell just short of a starting berth with a 52.74 score. While his BvP historicals and #3 order slot offered intrigue, the sheer efficiency output of our locked-in hitters relegated him to the bench; he remains our primary contingency if any last-minute lineup pivots emerge.\n\nWe are actively monitoring the status of **Bryson Stott**, who currently carries a \"Lineup Pending\" designation. If he slips from the projected #7 slot, his value could see a slight contraction, though his 13% platoon edge against Grant Holmes keeps his floor stable at 64.56. Elsewhere, **Cal Raleigh** and **Taylor Ward** represent strong starts, with **Taylor Ward** capitalizing on an elite #1 order position to maximize his at-bats against Cantillo. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Jung Hoo Lee**, whose 47.16 score is under pressure; he is a candidate for a quick sub if mid-game conditions sour, ensuring we preserve our game caps while maintaining tactical flexibility.",
